<subSubSection pageId="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1647,1997]" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1756,1781]" pageId="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Data are insufficient to define its distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[904,1009,1756,1781]" name="Romania" pageId="1">Romania</collectingCountry>
. We found it occurring in two slow flowing shaded streams, both rich with 
<taxonomicName box="[595,671,1793,1816]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Lemna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[595,671,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="1">Lemna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. and 
<taxonomicName box="[764,832,1791,1816]" class="Liliopsida" family="Typhaceae" genus="Typha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[764,832,1791,1816]" italics="true" pageId="1">Typha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. The altitude does not exceed 
<quantity box="[1207,1278,1791,1816]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="1" unit="m" value="150.0">150 m</quantity>
a.s.l. (
<figureCitation box="[1353,1421,1791,1816]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1205,1227]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,560,1176]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,553,1184]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Boxplots representing the altitudinal ranges of Veliidae in Romania." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/234010/files/figure.png" pageId="1">
Fig. 
<number box="[1405,1421,1791,1816]" pageId="1" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
). It overwinters as an adult (
<bibRefCitation author="Wroblewski" box="[448,653,1828,1853]" pageId="1" refString="Wroblewski, A. (1980) Pluskwiaki (Heteroptera). Fauna slodkowodna Polski. Vol. 8. Panstwowe Wydawnictwo Naukowe, Warszawa &amp; Poznan, 156 pp. [In Polish]" type="book" year="1980">
Wróblewski 
<number box="[593,653,1828,1852]" pageId="1" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). At both sites, it was found co-existing with 
<taxonomicName box="[1161,1307,1828,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Microvelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="reticulata">
<emphasis box="[1161,1184,1829,1852]" italics="true" pageId="1">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1199,1307,1828,1853]" italics="true" pageId="1">reticulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1647,1997]" pageId="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,452,1863,1888]" pageId="1">General distribution.</emphasis>
Holarctic species distributed from 
<collectingCountry box="[850,1040,1863,1888]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="1">United Kingdom</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1180,1250,1863,1888]" name="China" pageId="1">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1262,1346,1863,1888]" name="Canada" pageId="1">Canada</collectingCountry>
and the north of the 
<collectingCountry box="[295,450,1900,1925]" name="United States of America" pageId="1">United States</collectingCountry>
. In Europe it reaches as far south as 
<collectingCountry box="[879,958,1901,1924]" name="France" pageId="1">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1077,1900,1924]" name="Germany" pageId="1">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1090,1175,1900,1925]" name="Austria" pageId="1">Austria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1189,1287,1901,1925]" name="Hungary" pageId="1">Hungary</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1346,1436,1900,1925]" name="Ukraine" pageId="1">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
being absent in southern Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Putshkov" box="[525,837,1935,1960]" pageId="1" refString="Putshkov, V. G. &amp; Putshkov, P. V. (1996) Heteroptera of the Ukraine: Check list and distribution. Ukrainian Academy of Sciences, Institute of Zoology &amp; Russian Academy of Sciences, Zoological Institute, St. Petersburg, 109 pp." type="book" year="1996">
Putshkov &amp; Putshkov 
<number box="[778,837,1935,1960]" pageId="1" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rabitsch" box="[848,1113,1935,1960]" pageId="1" refString="Rabitsch, W. &amp; Zettel, H. (2000) Zur Wasserwanzenfauna (Heteroptera: Gerromorpha, Nepomorpha) des nordlichen Osterreich. Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 32, 1257 - 1268." type="journal article" year="2000">
Rabitsch &amp; Zettel 
<number box="[1054,1113,1936,1960]" pageId="1" value="2000.0">2000</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Aukema" box="[1125,1349,1935,1960]" pageId="1" refString="Aukema, B., Rieger, C. &amp; Rabitsch, W. (2013) Catalogue of the Heteroptera of the Palaearctic Region. VI. Supplement. The Netherlands Entomological Society, Amsterdam, xxiii + 629 pp." type="book" year="2013">
Aukema 
